ions;</p><p>Maintain Executive&#39;s appointment schedule by planning and scheduling meetings, conferences, teleconferences, and travel;</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>Assists in the coordination, organization and planning of meetings and functions with internal and external stakeholders (executives, employees, board members, customers and investors). This may include coordination of all travel logistics, i.e., itineraries, appointments, locations, transportation, etc.</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>Maintain office supplies inventory by checking stock to determine inventory level; anticipating needed supplies; evaluating new office products; placing and expediting orders for supplies; verifying receipt of supplies;</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>Organize and maintain electronic and paper files;</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>Maintain administrative forms and manuals;</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>Extreme attention to detail and follow-through;</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>Strong judgment and decision-making ability;</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>Outstanding interpersonal and customer service skills;</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>Exceptional organization skills with ability to handle sensitive confidential information in a professional manner;</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>Discretion, judgment, tact and diplomacy are a must;</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>Available to work flexible hours for special requests/projects that arise outside of normal business hours;</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>Ability to work well under pressure in an ever-changing environment while maintaining poise and professionalism;</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>Technologically savvy with advanced computer proficiency with Microsoft Office suite;</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>Ability to prioritize workload and multi-task;</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>Work independently, as well as partnering and team collaboration with other administrative assistants reporting to senior executives.</p><p>Qualifications:</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>Successful candidates will typically have the following skill set:</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>Administrative experience supporting high level executives;</p><p>Advance computer proficiency with Microsoft Office;</p><p>Experience with heavy calendar and travel scheduling (both domestic and internationally with emphasis on travel to Asia);</p><p>Ability to multi task and execute projects with quality and on time delivery;</p><p>Strong communication skills and the ability to work independently;</p><p>Available to work flexible hours for special requests/projects that arise outside of normal business hours.</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>At Entegris we are committed to providing equal opportunity to all employees and applicants. Our policy is to recruit, hire, train, and reward employees for their individual abilities, achievements and experience without regard to race, color, religion, sexual orientation, age, national origin, disability, marital or military status.</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>#LI-MF1</p><p>#LI-ATS</p><p>ENT789</p><br /><br /><div style="text-align:left;padding-bottom: 20px;"><a href="/frca-apply/bj0cnz" id="ApplyBottomLink" target="_blank" class="bigBlueButtonLink" rel="nofollow" onclick="javascript:setTimeout(&quot;window.location.href = &#39;/post-resume?jid=bj0cnz&#39;;&quot;,1500); return true;">Go to apply&nbsp;<img src="/Images/applyarrow.png" height="21x;" width="16px;" alt="" /></a></div></div></div></div><div style="background-color: #fcfcfc; max-width: 400px;" class="sideBar"><div style="text-align:left; vertical-align:top; padding-left:5px;"><h4 style="padding-bottom:7px;">Similar Jobs</h4><p style="padding-bottom:4px;"><a href="/job/bi09la/administrator-executive-billerica-ma" rel="nofollow" onclick="ga(&#39;send&#39;, &#39;event&#39;, &#39;Links&#39;, &#39;JobToJob&#39;, &#39;0&#39;);">Executive Administrator</a><br/><span style="font-size:small" cl